Oblarg:

gravity feedforward but your process variable is not in rotations

So if you left it in Volts/ rad/s instead of converting?

Oblarg:

(which REV seems to have chosen as canonical - good choice!)

It’s all about consistency. I prefer SI, but it’s like Fahrenheit Celsius. One just makes more sense. Though degrees help me when explaining it casually (just not using it in the implementation).

Also rotations good choice, rpm bad choice. They need to fix that.
